<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-69-0027 </DOCNO><TEXT>Reviews the progress of the US coal industry during 1988 with specialreference to the following: acid rain legislation; groundwater contaminationand its prevention; global warming; Clean Coal technologies; transportationsystems (rail and inland waterways); foreign trade in coal; plant closures;occupational safety and health; surface mining and leasing; regulationof the electric power industry; and production and consumption of coal.For each issue, legislation introduced in the House of Representativesand Senate, and the policy adopted by the National Coal Association,is described. The outlook for 1989 is presented. 3 figs.</TEXT></DOC>